post_text:
Hello ACEA Families!

The first day of school is Tuesday, September 8, 2020. There are two opportunities for returning students to complete registration for 2020-21. New students do not have to come unless they receive a phone call to do so.

Thursday, August 27 11:00 am â€“ 12:30 pm

Wednesday, September 2 1:00 â€“ 3:00 pm

Paperwork that is needed has been reduced so this should go quickly and will be done from your car. Please pull up to the ACEA entrance door and someone will come to your car with the paperwork to complete. If you did paperwork at last weekâ€™s food drive, you do not need to come. If neither of these times work for you, please contact the office 631-5202 x 215.

Next week there will be additional communication for transportation, on-line learning schedules, and information on safety protocols/procedures for face-to-face instructions.

Thank you!

Michelle Zielinski, Principal

*Volunteer Information*

A wonderful team of volunteers from Meridian Public Schools and the United Way of Midland County have created two volunteer registration booths in Sanford, one at the intersection of Center St. and Oak, and one at the pharmacy across from Sanford Food and Pride. If you are planning on heading to the Sanford area to volunteer, you will be directed to one of these booths, and dispatched to a part of the community that needs help.

If you live in the Sanford area and need to request help, call (989)495-2284, and they will do their best to dispatch volunteers to assist you. If you have a neighbor that needs help, you are able to call in on their behalf as well!

ðŸ“£ðŸ¥ªPandemic EBT ProgramðŸ¥ªðŸ“£

The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer Program (P-EBT) by Michigan Department of Health and Human Services provides temporary funding to address emergency food needs for families affected by the pandemic.

P-EBT food assistance benefits will go to Michigan families with students ages 5-18 that are eligible for free or reduced-price school meals. This includes families currently receiving Food Assistance Program benefits, as well as those not currently enrolled in the program.

*No application is necessary for eligible families to receive P-EBT benefits.

.
.
.

DIAL 211 for more agencies listed to HELP!
www.211nemichigan.org

March 25 at 11:52 AM Â·

Good morning ACEA staff and students! It's Manatee Appreciation Day folks, but I'm surprised people aren't appreciating manatees on the regular. I thought that was kinda just a thing we did??

On this day in the year 708, Constantine began his reign as Pope (not the MOST recent I guess, but that's my brother's name, so I had to do it).

It's so boring right now. I can feel the cabin fever creeping in. But maybe that's just the COVID-19?

Anywho! Here's a quote from "Charlotte's Web", "Wilbur didn't want food, he wanted love." And I just wanted something to do! We'll make it through this together though!

Much love!

Lily Martinezâ€ŽAcademic & Career Education Academy
March 24 at 2:18 PM Â·

Good afternoon ACEA staff and students (that's a new one!)! It's National Chocolate Covered Raisin Day (yum) AND the first day of our freaking LOCKDOWN! And it's Alex's birthday!

On this day in 1989, Exxon's Valdez spilled 11.3 million gallons of oil off the Alaskan coast. All that pollution, gotta love it!

Things are getting pretty serious now, guys. Just stay inside and stay safe. I know times are tough, but make sure you utilize the resources available to us.

A quote by Jorge Luis Borges, "Reality is not always probable, or likely." This is definitely something I'm feeling right now. I never could have imagined this happening yet here it is, right at our front door. Just remember, we're all here for each other.

Much love!

Lily Martinezâ€ŽAcademic & Career Education Academy
March 23 at 11:31 AM Â·

Good morning ACEA staff and students! It's National Chips and Dip Day. So make sure you get some before the food hoarders come out!

On this day in 2005, an explosion at the Texas City Refinery killed 15 workers. All that bright and cheery stuff, ya know?

"Just because you're offended doesn't mean you're right." -Ricky Gervais

Time for another round of hour cuts at Michaels. So we'll see how things go! Nevermind, apparently Gov. Whitmer has locked us in! It's quarantine time, boys!

Aside from all of the craziness that's been going on, I haven't been this happy in a while. I'm not going to worry about the things I can't control, and the things I can control are looking pretty amazing at the moment.

Much love! Stay safe out there!

Lily Martinezâ€ŽAcademic & Career Education Academy
March 22 at 6:50 AM Â·

Good morning ACEA staff and students! It's National Bavarian Crepes Day. So that's cool, I guess.

On this day in 1973, the U.S. Supreme Court ruled, in Eisenstadt v. Baird, that unmarried people have the same right to contraception as married people.

Nothing too interesting for you folks today. Come get curbside pickup at Michaels though!

Now, a quote for you guys, "Never hurry and never worry!" by Charlotte, from "Charlotte's Web". We're taking this all one day at a time. I'm pretty bummed out my senior year has been so interrupted, but I'm dealing with it day by day. We're going to get back to normal and have an amazing prom! Take care guys!

P.S. A quote by Mark Cosby, CEO of Michaels, "Until further notice, Michaels Team Members at the corporate office have the option to work from home." You can't make this stuff up.

Much love!

March 21 at 1:44 AM Â·

Good morning ACEA staff and students! Today is National Quilting Day, which some of you might like to take up since it's crazy out there!

On this day in 2019, a Bangladeshi woman with two uteruses safely gave birth to her TWINS only 26 days after having given birth to another kid! No thank you!

Guys, we're living in a time that'll be talked about in history classes. Just take care everyone. Stay in when you can and use this time to get ahead in classes.

A quote to leave you guys off with, by Martin Luther King Jr., "We must accept finite disappointment, but we must never lose infinite hope."

P.S. I have a surprise in the works for you all when we get back!

FREE meals to ANY child 18 and younger (up to 26 with a disability), beginning today, Monday, March 16. Breakfast and lunch, Monday - Friday, from 8:00-10:00 am & 11:00-2:00 pm. Meals delivered to your car, served at the Freeland Elementary back entrance. Pull up, let us know how many children you are providing meals for, and we will bring the meals to you. shared_text:
Midland County Emergency Food Pantry Network
March 13 at 11:41 AM Â·

We are taking extra precautions keep all of our services going and to be able to continue to serve those in need.

Here are where we are today on the programs and will keep you updated as changes and more information is available:

MOBILE FOOD PANTRIES:

The clients remain in their cars for registration and distribution. We will forgo signatures and all hand washing including hand sanitizer will be used by volunteers.

PANTRIES-
All u-pick pantries will go to non u-pick. Volunteers will preload boxes and deliver them to your cars. We will also waive signatures and be using best hand washing practices within the pantries.

BACKPACK- Since schools are closed for three weeks we are working with the schools, United Way and The Food Bank to figure out exactly to process here. Stay tuned as we work through the best way to serve the children that rely on food from the schools.

SENIOR DELIVERY Will operate as usual. Maintain minimal contact between volunteer and recipient.

post_text:
Are you looking for a Free Public High School that offers a different approach to traditional schools?
Do you need night classes? We have them.
Do you need individualized instruction? We do that.
Missing that personal connection? We are a caring and supportive school.
Check out ACEA- Academic & Career Education Academy. We offer small class sizes, personalized instruction to high school students completing grades 9-12 or young adults working on their GED. Call 374-ACEA, stop by the ETC Building on M20, or check out our web page at aceaofmidland.com.
